name: np.array()
describe: Creates an array from a list or tuple.

name: np.linspace()
describe: Creates an array of evenly spaced values over a specified range.

name: np.arange()
describe: Creates an array of evenly spaced values within a given range.

name: np.random.uniform()
describe: Generates random numbers from a uniform distribution.

name: np.random.randint()
describe: Generates random integers within a specified range.

name: np.random.random()
describe: Generates random numbers from a uniform distribution between 0 and 1.

name: np.logspace()
describe: Creates an array of evenly spaced values on a logarithmic scale.

name: np.zeros()
describe: Creates an array filled with zeros.

name: np.ones()
describe: Creates an array filled with ones.

name: np.full()
describe: Creates an array filled with a specified value.

name: np.identity()
describe: Creates an identity matrix.

name: np.min()
describe: Returns the minimum value in an array.

name: np.max()
describe: Returns the maximum value in an array.

name: np.mean()
describe: Computes the mean of an array.

name: np.median()
describe: Computes the median of an array.

name: np.std()
describe: Computes the standard deviation of an array.

name: np.var()
describe: Computes the variance of an array.

name: np.mean()
describe: Computes the mean of an array.

name: np.digitize()
describe: Returns the indices of the bins to which each value in an array belongs.

name: np.reshape()
describe: Reshapes an array into a specified shape.

name: np.expand_dims()
describe: Adds a new axis to an array.

name: np.squeeze()
describe: Removes single-dimensional entries from the shape of an array.

name: np.count_nonzero()
describe: Counts the number of non-zero elements in an array.

name: np.argwhere()
describe: Finds the indices of array elements that meet a condition.

name: np.argmax()
describe: Returns the indices of the maximum values along an axis.

name: np.argmin()
describe: Returns the indices of the minimum values along an axis.

name: np.argsort()
describe: Returns the indices that would sort an array.

name: np.sort()
describe: Sorts an array.

name: np.abs()
describe: Computes the absolute value element-wise.

name: np.round()
describe: Rounds the elements of an array to the nearest integer.

name: np.clip()
describe: Clips the values in an array to a specified range.

name: np.where()
describe: Returns elements chosen from two arrays depending on a condition.

name: np.put()
describe: Replaces specified elements in an array.

name: np.copyto()
describe: Copies values from one array to another.

name: np.intersect1d()
describe: Finds the intersection of two arrays.

name: np.union1d()
describe: Finds the union of two arrays.

name: np.setdiff1d()
describe: Finds the set difference of two arrays.

name: np.unique()
describe: Finds the unique elements of an array.

name: np.hsplit()
describe: Splits an array into multiple sub-arrays horizontally.

name: np.vsplit()
describe: Splits an array into multiple sub-arrays vertically.

name: np.hstack()
describe: Stacks arrays in sequence horizontally.

name: np.vstack()
describe: Stacks arrays in sequence vertically.

name: np.allclose()
describe: Returns True if two arrays are element-wise equal within a tolerance.

name: np.repeat()
describe: Repeats elements of an array.

name: np.tile()
describe: Constructs an array by repeating a sequence.

name: np.einsum()
describe: Evaluates the Einstein summation convention on the operands.

name: np.dot()
describe: Computes the dot product of two arrays.

name: np.concatenate()
describe: Joins a sequence of arrays along an existing axis.

name: np.histogram()
describe: Computes the histogram of a set of data.

name: np.percentile()
describe: Computes the q-th percentile of the data.
